WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:19.420
One Piece

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.420
Wano Arc

4
00:01:42.080 --> 00:01:46.330
<b>Shutenmaru</b>

5
00:01:47.980 --> 00:01:49.750
It's a secret mission!

6
00:01:49.750 --> 00:01:51.060
Alright!

7
00:01:52.270 --> 00:01:54.050
That'll be our decisive battle!

8
00:01:54.050 --> 00:01:56.170
The battle will take place...

9
00:01:58.020 --> 00:02:00.030
on an island called Onigashima...

10
00:02:01.150 --> 00:02:04.850
where Kaido and his Beast Pirates
have made their base!

11
00:02:04.850 --> 00:02:06.100
An island?!

12
00:02:06.100 --> 00:02:10.770
You mean we have to cross
the sea within Wano?

13
00:02:10.770 --> 00:02:12.690
That's right!

14
00:02:12.690 --> 00:02:18.740
With the island practically visible from the coast,
larger sailing vessels aren't required for the journey.

15
00:02:18.740 --> 00:02:21.200
However, we'll still need a boat...

16
00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:24.060
if we are to raid Onigashima.

17
00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:27.550
Well, we can worry about boats later.

18
00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:30.330
When are we doing this?

19
00:02:30.330 --> 00:02:33.000
The battle will be on
the day of the Fire Festival.

20
00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:38.720
The Fire Festival is a grand festival
for the people of the capital.

21
00:02:38.720 --> 00:02:43.680
Kaido is considered
a guardian deity of this country,

22
00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:49.780
and on that day, Orochi will lead the Shogun's
procession to Onigashima to pay tribute to him.

23
00:02:49.780 --> 00:02:52.880
But all that is merely pretense!

24
00:02:52.880 --> 00:02:59.070
In reality, they'll be holding a banquet for
the officials and the Beast Pirates.

25
00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:01.280
I see...

26
00:03:01.280 --> 00:03:06.160
So we'll beat the hell out of
those partying, drunken fools

27
00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:08.840
and take out their leaders!

28
00:03:08.840 --> 00:03:09.500
But...!

29
00:03:09.500 --> 00:03:17.730
Okiku, once you see my heroics, you might
fall for me over that perverted samurai!

30
00:03:17.730 --> 00:03:20.630
Oh, no, Sir Sanji! I believe
you've got the wrong idea!

31
00:03:20.630 --> 00:03:27.150
I have a wife and Okiku is my comrade,
so that is the extent of our relationship...

32
00:03:27.150 --> 00:03:30.020
Otsuru is doing well, by the way.

33
00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:31.390
You saw her?!

34
00:03:31.390 --> 00:03:34.100
I did, and she didn't recognize me.

35
00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:35.810
Is that so...?

36
00:03:35.810 --> 00:03:37.940
I'm glad she's okay...

37
00:03:37.940 --> 00:03:42.990
but I must refrain from seeing her
until we accomplish our great task.

38
00:03:42.990 --> 00:03:44.560
Sir Kin...

39
00:03:44.560 --> 00:03:48.410
Married men shouldn't be popular
with the ladies! It's not fair!

40
00:03:48.410 --> 00:03:51.850
Okiku, please dote on me, too!

41
00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:53.300
Just shut up...

42
00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:57.340
Sanji, Kiku is unbelievably strong!

43
00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:02.370
She's not just lovely but also strong?

44
00:04:03.220 --> 00:04:05.010
How perfect.

45
00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:11.480
Now, I drew a symbol that implies the date
and rendezvous point for our battle.

46
00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:13.640
Two birds ablaze...

47
00:04:14.270 --> 00:04:15.980
over a pit viper or a habu...

48
00:04:15.980 --> 00:04:19.610
and a reversed crescent moon
to signify rebellion!

49
00:04:20.110 --> 00:04:23.820
The day of the Fire Festival. At twilight. The second hour of the bird.

50
00:04:23.820 --> 00:04:26.240
At Habu Port."

51
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:31.950
Overseas, "The second hour of the bird"
means 5:30 or 6:00 in the evening.

52
00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:37.080
Do not worry. The people
of Wano will understand.

53
00:04:40.220 --> 00:04:47.340
We must distribute these flyers to those who
bear the mark of the moon on their left ankles!

54
00:04:47.340 --> 00:04:50.190
The symbol indicates their desire to rebel.

55
00:04:50.190 --> 00:04:52.310
They are our allies!

56
00:04:52.310 --> 00:04:56.420
They could be anywhere in Wano...

57
00:04:56.420 --> 00:04:59.150
so in order to reach
as many people as possible,

58
00:04:59.150 --> 00:05:02.400
we have positioned our friends
throughout the country.

59
00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:09.330
Sir Zorojuro and Sir Usohachi are already
carrying out this task in the capital.

60
00:05:09.330 --> 00:05:13.120
Ah, I don't think Zoro is helping...

61
00:05:15.660 --> 00:05:20.990
Furthermore, so that we don't lose
our way after arriving at Onigashima,

62
00:05:20.990 --> 00:05:26.760
we are trying to obtain the blueprints of
Kaido's mansion from the carpenter who designed it.

63
00:05:26.760 --> 00:05:30.490
So we procured employment
for Sir Franosuke under him.

64
00:05:30.490 --> 00:05:35.320
As for Madam Orobi, since we need to know
every move Orochi's forces make,

65
00:05:35.320 --> 00:05:41.570
I asked her to pose as a geisha
in order to secure an audience with Orochi!

66
00:05:41.570 --> 00:05:43.930
I heard she has become very popular.

67
00:05:43.930 --> 00:05:47.200
I wanna see Robin in her geisha outfit!

68
00:05:47.200 --> 00:05:51.800
And now, I would like to delegate
tasks to the rest of you.

69
00:05:51.800 --> 00:05:56.760
Sir Brook's ability can help us procure
food supplies in the capital.

70
00:05:56.760 --> 00:05:59.130
What...? It can?

71
00:05:59.130 --> 00:06:03.840
Madam Nami's manipulation of the weather is
like ninjutsu, so she'll pose as a kunoichi!

72
00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:05.710
That's a female ninja, right?!

73
00:06:07.220 --> 00:06:09.280
The kunoichi Onami!

74
00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:12.510
Nami... A kunoichi?!

75
00:06:12.510 --> 00:06:17.990
Sir Sanji's cooking will be able to gather
people together, helping us find recruits.

76
00:06:18.890 --> 00:06:20.570
Sir Sanji?

77
00:06:20.570 --> 00:06:21.810
Yeah, leave it to me!

78
00:06:21.810 --> 00:06:23.360
What about me?

79
00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:29.710
Madam Carrot and Sir Chopper, I want you
to go with Kiku and assist Inuarashi.

80
00:06:29.710 --> 00:06:32.320
Kin'emon! I wanna be a ninja, too!

81
00:06:32.320 --> 00:06:33.850
So shall it be!

82
00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:38.250
I will provide clothes
that are suited to your roles!

83
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:42.770
Now, put a leaf on your head
and brace yourselves!

84
00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:45.520
Are you ready?!

85
00:06:46.110 --> 00:06:47.420
Here it goes!

86
00:06:47.450 --> 00:06:49.050
My special magical ability!

87
00:06:49.970 --> 00:06:52.470
Garb-Garb Technique!

88
00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:53.470
Poof!

89
00:07:03.940 --> 00:07:06.320
Nami my sweet!

90
00:07:06.320 --> 00:07:08.360
Ninja!

91
00:07:08.360 --> 00:07:12.620
Since you're wearing appropriate Wanese
clothing, it's time to set about your tasks.

92
00:07:12.620 --> 00:07:14.030
Wait, Kin'emon!

93
00:07:14.030 --> 00:07:16.490
Is this really how a kunoichi dresses?!

94
00:07:16.490 --> 00:07:19.120
That's how a kunoichi...

95
00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:20.660
should dress!

96
00:07:20.660 --> 00:07:22.750
Are you kidding me?!

97
00:07:25.080 --> 00:07:27.490
Now then, allow me to summon your guide.

98
00:07:27.490 --> 00:07:30.170
She is a real kunoichi.

99
00:07:30.170 --> 00:07:32.630
A real kunoichi!

100
00:07:32.760 --> 00:07:34.930
Now this is a treat!

101
00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:36.850
Shinobu!

102
00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:44.260
What?!

103
00:07:46.490 --> 00:07:47.360
Did you call?!

104
00:07:47.360 --> 00:07:49.990
How they should dress?!

105
00:07:51.450 --> 00:07:53.410
– What?!
– What?!

106
00:07:55.550 --> 00:07:56.660
I won't...

107
00:07:57.420 --> 00:07:58.580
lose hope...

108
00:07:58.580 --> 00:08:02.790
Oh no! He's going into shock!

109
00:08:02.790 --> 00:08:06.170
Kin'emon! Is this just your taste?

110
00:08:06.170 --> 00:08:11.420
Kunoichi are either sexy or frumpy.
Indeed, there are only two types...

111
00:08:16.760 --> 00:08:18.680
Maybe if I tighten it up...

112
00:08:18.680 --> 00:08:21.670
Brook, what are you disguised as?

113
00:08:21.670 --> 00:08:25.360
A person who wears panties on his head.

114
00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:28.010
Or so I thought!

115
00:08:31.860 --> 00:08:34.460
Isn't it nice...

116
00:08:34.460 --> 00:08:35.950
to be young?

117
00:08:35.950 --> 00:08:38.500
My name is Shinobu!

118
00:08:37.490 --> 00:08:41.910
<b>Shinobu
A Veteran Kunoichi</b>

119
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:41.910
I used to be like a younger
sister to Master Kin.

120
00:08:41.910 --> 00:08:43.570
But now...

121
00:08:44.890 --> 00:08:47.580
I'm known for my Seduction Technique.

122
00:08:47.580 --> 00:08:49.150
Nice to meet you.

123
00:08:49.890 --> 00:08:53.090
If it weren't for Nami,
my spirit would've been broken...

124
00:08:53.090 --> 00:08:55.550
No, Sanji!

125
00:08:56.090 --> 00:08:58.100
I understand, young man...

126
00:08:58.100 --> 00:09:00.470
Mature women...

127
00:09:01.770 --> 00:09:04.690
are like deadly weapons...

128
00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:05.560
All right!

129
00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:08.280
Until the rendezvous, we will split up...

130
00:09:08.780 --> 00:09:12.230
but there are three samurai
in particular we need to find!

131
00:09:13.360 --> 00:09:16.450
If we can recruit them,
they will be an added boon!

132
00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:18.190
Kawamatsu.

133
00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:19.470
Ashura Doji.

134
00:09:19.470 --> 00:09:20.910
Denjiro.

135
00:09:20.910 --> 00:09:25.160
Like us, those three served
as retainers to Lord Oden!

136
00:09:26.670 --> 00:09:29.920
Let's do this! All of our allies are in place!

137
00:09:31.630 --> 00:09:37.590
Our targets are Emperor Kaido
and the hateful Shogun Kurozumi Orochi!

138
00:09:37.590 --> 00:09:42.060
We act two weeks from now,
on the night of the Fire Festival!

139
00:09:42.850 --> 00:09:45.730
We will raid...

140
00:09:45.730 --> 00:09:49.520
Kaido's home, Onigashima!

141
00:09:57.950 --> 00:10:00.280
<b>Okobore 
Town</b>

142
00:10:04.950 --> 00:10:06.750
– What?!
– What?!

143
00:10:18.300 --> 00:10:19.680
"Heaven"

144
00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:30.600
<b>Boss Shutenmaru
Mount Atama Thieves</b>

145
00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:42.550
Hello there!

146
00:10:44.750 --> 00:10:45.790
Do it!

147
00:10:49.410 --> 00:10:52.580
These fools have the good stuff!

148
00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:52.580
"Sake"

149
00:10:52.580 --> 00:10:55.380
Give that back! Luffytaro gave...!

150
00:10:55.380 --> 00:10:58.030
Luffytaro gave it to us!

151
00:10:58.030 --> 00:10:59.700
Shut up!

152
00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:00.760
Mother!

153
00:11:00.760 --> 00:11:05.730
Oh? There's even fruit,
sake, and rice! The nerve...

154
00:11:05.730 --> 00:11:08.860
Give that back! It's for my grandson!

155
00:11:09.640 --> 00:11:13.360
Shut up, old man! Hurry up
and kick the bucket already–

156
00:11:23.790 --> 00:11:25.950
Who the hell...

157
00:11:25.950 --> 00:11:28.910
pulled a stunt like this?!

158
00:11:28.910 --> 00:11:33.120
Giving people food and acting like a hero?!

159
00:11:33.120 --> 00:11:35.710
It's nothing but a pipe dream for you people.

160
00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:39.090
You may have finally gotten some food...

161
00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:42.800
but we're taking it; that's how it's gonna be!

162
00:11:42.800 --> 00:11:48.220
There are no samurai left to the poor folk!

163
00:11:49.220 --> 00:11:55.960
No one left in this country is man enough...

164
00:11:55.960 --> 00:11:59.190
to lead our powerful samurai.

165
00:12:00.550 --> 00:12:05.410
Wano is finished!

166
00:12:09.410 --> 00:12:11.630
Got that, you old hag?

167
00:12:11.630 --> 00:12:18.170
Even if you somehow cling to life,
nothing will change this cruel reality.

168
00:12:25.590 --> 00:12:28.460
Let me put you out of your misery!

169
00:12:31.270 --> 00:12:32.960
Please run!

170
00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:34.500
Grandma!

171
00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:44.610
I believe in Lady Otoki's words...

172
00:12:47.170 --> 00:12:49.160
She's dead!

173
00:12:49.710 --> 00:12:52.480
I know that the nine samurai...

174
00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:55.580
will fulfill Lord Oden's wish!

175
00:12:55.580 --> 00:12:57.390
Ridiculous!

176
00:12:57.390 --> 00:13:01.090
A war cannot be fought without a leader!

177
00:13:12.470 --> 00:13:14.680
Boss Shutenmaru! That's...!

178
00:13:34.820 --> 00:13:37.540
I finally get to meet...

179
00:13:42.650 --> 00:13:44.880
the head of the thieves brigade.

180
00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:48.050
<b>Jack
Superstar, Beast Pirates</b>

181
00:13:45.730 --> 00:13:48.710
A-A-A-A monster!

182
00:13:48.710 --> 00:13:53.770
A pirate named Straw Hat Luffy
should have come through here...

183
00:13:55.000 --> 00:14:00.560
I don't suppose your demeanor will change
if I tell you I don't know the guy?

184
00:14:01.120 --> 00:14:03.650
Don't push your luck.

185
00:14:04.290 --> 00:14:05.690
Huh?!

186
00:14:05.690 --> 00:14:09.580
The only reason we let you live...

187
00:14:09.580 --> 00:14:13.770
is because Kaido wants you as a subordinate.

188
00:14:14.470 --> 00:14:18.540
It doesn't mean I have to show you respect!

189
00:14:21.650 --> 00:14:24.300
Then, I'll give you my answer...

190
00:14:26.800 --> 00:14:29.380
to that invitation!

191
00:14:37.470 --> 00:14:41.080
Hey, Kin'emon, I understand your plan.

192
00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:44.080
But there's still one thing
that doesn't make sense.

193
00:14:44.770 --> 00:14:49.570
You said that Oden defeated
Ashura Doji over twenty years ago...

194
00:14:49.570 --> 00:14:55.740
So why is he among the allies
you want us to find?

195
00:14:57.270 --> 00:14:59.580
That's a fair question.

196
00:15:00.270 --> 00:15:05.770
Ashura Doji mended his ways
after Lord Oden defeated him.

197
00:15:05.770 --> 00:15:09.170
Indeed, he pledged his loyalty to him.

198
00:15:10.530 --> 00:15:11.470
However...

199
00:15:11.470 --> 00:15:16.950
We heard he became the head of the Mount
Atama Thieves under the name Shutenmaru...

200
00:15:16.950 --> 00:15:19.680
and has returned to a life of crime.

201
00:15:21.310 --> 00:15:24.270
Hmm, thieves, huh?

202
00:15:25.620 --> 00:15:26.690
So then...

203
00:15:27.490 --> 00:15:29.900
is he strong?

204
00:15:30.660 --> 00:15:36.450
Yes, and it wouldn't be too much of a stretch
to say he might be the strongest samurai.

205
00:15:42.250 --> 00:15:43.430
I see!

206
00:16:06.220 --> 00:16:09.070
Don't mess with a samurai!

207
00:16:17.370 --> 00:16:19.080
Master Jack!

208
00:16:19.080 --> 00:16:21.290
Damn you...

209
00:17:02.540 --> 00:17:05.770
Get back! Shutenmaru and Master Jack...

210
00:17:05.770 --> 00:17:07.330
...are starting to fight!

211
00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:10.750
We're doomed!

212
00:17:54.510 --> 00:17:58.340
Ever since he died...

213
00:18:00.220 --> 00:18:03.140
I've been looking for a way
to join him in death.

214
00:18:09.480 --> 00:18:10.690
However...

215
00:18:12.270 --> 00:18:16.820
My death won't come by a flunky like you!

216
00:18:16.820 --> 00:18:18.610
Cut the crap!

217
00:18:32.090 --> 00:18:33.710
I...

218
00:18:36.050 --> 00:18:39.080
should have died back then!

219
00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:45.770
Living is such a pain.

220
00:19:27.600 --> 00:19:30.190
Master Jack!

221
00:19:30.800 --> 00:19:32.520
L-Look... The sky!

222
00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:37.610
No way... Why?

223
00:19:39.900 --> 00:19:44.030
Why did he come in person?

224
00:19:44.030 --> 00:19:46.750
I-Is it because of me? Is it?

225
00:19:46.750 --> 00:19:49.120
Did he come to execute me?!

226
00:19:50.710 --> 00:19:52.260
Why, all of a sudden...?

227
00:19:52.270 --> 00:19:53.710
Is it gonna rain?

228
00:19:54.600 --> 00:19:55.710
No!

229
00:19:55.710 --> 00:19:58.670
Hey, Straw Hat! Get over here now!

230
00:19:59.290 --> 00:20:00.760
What's wrong, Traffy?

231
00:20:03.180 --> 00:20:04.680
What the...?

232
00:20:19.150 --> 00:20:20.380
Lord Momonosuke!

233
00:20:20.380 --> 00:20:22.800
What?! Lord Momonosuke can turn into a...

234
00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:24.490
...d-dragon?!

235
00:20:25.360 --> 00:20:31.060
I will explain later, but yes,
he is able to morph into this!

236
00:20:31.060 --> 00:20:33.160
Of all things...

237
00:20:33.160 --> 00:20:36.460
it had to be the form of a damn dragon!

238
00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:41.550
We're in trouble, Straw Hat.

239
00:20:52.070 --> 00:20:53.820
Move! Outta the way!

240
00:20:57.050 --> 00:20:59.210
I don't believe it...

241
00:20:59.210 --> 00:21:00.370
Why...?

242
00:21:09.910 --> 00:21:12.250
Hey, Jack.

243
00:21:12.720 --> 00:21:14.010
Yes, sir...

244
00:21:16.580 --> 00:21:19.920
Bring those brats...

245
00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:23.060
to me at once.

246
00:21:26.840 --> 00:21:29.100
Is that... a dragon?!

247
00:21:29.850 --> 00:21:32.140
Things can't get any worse...

248
00:21:32.880 --> 00:21:33.850
That's...

249
00:21:36.780 --> 00:21:38.190
Kaido!

250
00:21:38.850 --> 00:21:40.020
So that's...

251
00:21:41.670 --> 00:21:43.320
Kaido!

252
00:22:19.810 --> 00:22:21.940
So Kaido is a dragon?!

253
00:22:24.050 --> 00:22:25.070
Yes...

254
00:22:31.730 --> 00:22:34.620
What you see before you is Kaido!

255
00:22:42.090 --> 00:22:43.630
He is able...

256
00:22:46.260 --> 00:22:49.170
to transform into a dragon!

257
00:22:58.000 --> 00:23:00.190
Okobore Town is over there!

258
00:23:00.190 --> 00:23:05.370
But why would Kaido
come to Kuri all of a sudden?

259
00:23:05.370 --> 00:23:07.810
I'm sorry, Kin'emon.

260
00:23:07.810 --> 00:23:11.950
The truth is they identified me,
Straw Hat, and Zoro.

261
00:23:11.950 --> 00:23:12.950
What?!

262
00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:18.380
But that's all they know!
Our plan is still under wraps!

263
00:23:18.380 --> 00:23:20.080
"That's all they know"?!

264
00:23:20.080 --> 00:23:23.710
How the hell could you be so sloppy, Law?!

265
00:23:23.710 --> 00:23:27.990
You Straw Hat Pirates
don't have any right to blame me!

266
00:23:28.800 --> 00:23:31.220
Oh, I'm sure it was Luffy's fault.

267
00:23:31.220 --> 00:23:33.140
Well, we're sorry.

268
00:23:33.140 --> 00:23:35.560
He's probably looking for...

269
00:23:35.560 --> 00:23:38.350
me and Straw Hat.

270
00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:44.100
Kaido's Beast Pirates maintain...

271
00:23:44.100 --> 00:23:48.320
their overwhelming power
thanks to two key factors.

272
00:23:49.500 --> 00:23:54.280
First, the weapons that Kaido is
manufacturing in this country!

273
00:23:55.180 --> 00:24:03.000
Second, the underground trade of Caesar
and Doflamingo's manufactured SMILE devil fruits.

274
00:24:04.850 --> 00:24:09.760
We destroyed the source of that trade
with the factory on Punk Hazard...

275
00:24:10.340 --> 00:24:14.100
and captured Caesar who was
necessary for SMILE development.

276
00:24:18.850 --> 00:24:20.710
On top of that...

277
00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:23.480
we destroyed another factory in Dressrosa...

278
00:24:24.100 --> 00:24:29.030
where Doflamingo, Kaido's critical
trading partner, ruled.

279
00:24:29.360 --> 00:24:34.190
We also were key to the buyer
Doflamingo's arrest, bringing him to ruin...

280
00:24:36.030 --> 00:24:37.390
In short...

281
00:24:39.020 --> 00:24:42.010
we picked a fight with Kaido.

282
00:24:42.010 --> 00:24:44.120
So the only ones he's coming after are...

283
00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:47.410
me and Straw Hat!

284
00:24:51.420 --> 00:24:52.670
Hey, Luffy!

285
00:24:52.670 --> 00:24:54.650
Luffy, wait!

286
00:24:54.650 --> 00:24:55.620
Sir Luffy!

287
00:24:55.620 --> 00:24:58.010
Don't follow him! I'll go!

288
00:24:59.330 --> 00:25:02.560
If more of us get exposed,

289
00:25:02.560 --> 00:25:07.310
they'll find out that all of
the Straw Hat and Heart Pirates are here!

290
00:25:09.420 --> 00:25:11.610
It would kick off a giant manhunt!

291
00:25:16.570 --> 00:25:18.930
We need to think rationally.

292
00:25:18.930 --> 00:25:22.500
We're the only ones they've seen.

293
00:25:30.160 --> 00:25:31.960
Your plan is still safe!

294
00:25:32.890 --> 00:25:33.840
All right?

295
00:25:33.840 --> 00:25:36.510
Then, what are you two going to do?!

296
00:25:38.840 --> 00:25:41.010
I wish I could let things be...

297
00:25:42.310 --> 00:25:46.440
but Straw Hat has already gotten involved
with the people of this country.

298
00:25:55.580 --> 00:25:59.320
If his emotions take charge,
then our plan is doomed.

299
00:26:02.580 --> 00:26:07.330
This alliance will have been pointless if we
aren't all there on the day of execution.

300
00:26:09.530 --> 00:26:11.190
I'll take care of it.

301
00:26:12.000 --> 00:26:13.100
Room!

302
00:26:16.470 --> 00:26:19.050
No matter what, do not reveal yourselves!

303
00:26:21.140 --> 00:26:22.640
Shambles!

304
00:26:24.100 --> 00:26:25.930
– Captain!
– Captain!

305
00:26:33.620 --> 00:26:38.320
Damn it, Luffy! What did you do
while we were separated?

306
00:26:53.400 --> 00:26:56.170
Retreat to the forest, Mount Atama Thieves!

307
00:26:56.170 --> 00:26:58.840
We do not want to get involved with him!

308
00:27:16.710 --> 00:27:19.380
I heard rumors...

309
00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:23.990
about the mighty brigand living
deep in the mountains of Kuri.

310
00:27:23.990 --> 00:27:26.000
Shutenmaru.

311
00:27:31.250 --> 00:27:33.290
I...

312
00:27:33.290 --> 00:27:35.630
remember you...

313
00:27:58.630 --> 00:28:01.480
But let's not dwell on the past!

314
00:28:03.700 --> 00:28:06.870
If you bend the knee to me...

315
00:28:17.450 --> 00:28:20.970
it'll all be water under the bridge.

316
00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:48.280
Whoa! Smells like alcohol!

317
00:28:48.280 --> 00:28:51.700
Kaido, don't tell me you're drunk!

318
00:28:53.800 --> 00:28:57.280
You idiot! I'm not drunk!

319
00:28:57.880 --> 00:28:59.630
– He's drunk!
– He's drunk!

320
00:29:09.700 --> 00:29:12.730
What'll it be, Shutenmaru?

321
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:17.260
We can't get away! We'll have to fight him!

322
00:29:23.110 --> 00:29:26.420
Master Jack, I'm trying to stop
the bleeding, so don't move!

323
00:29:26.420 --> 00:29:30.990
He's so wasted... He could
lose his temper at any moment.

324
00:29:30.990 --> 00:29:33.580
We'd better get out of here.

325
00:29:33.580 --> 00:29:36.770
Right. But...

326
00:29:36.770 --> 00:29:41.250
the residents of Okobore Town
are valuable laborers for our factories!

327
00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:45.010
I'm all for setting an example...

328
00:29:45.010 --> 00:29:48.220
but if he wreaks havoc senselessly...

329
00:29:48.220 --> 00:29:50.240
he'll wipe out all of Kuri.

330
00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:55.260
Why didn't you tell me sooner, Kiku?!

331
00:29:55.260 --> 00:29:56.730
Apologies, Sir Kin!

332
00:29:56.730 --> 00:30:00.650
Why don't you go back?! I will save Tsuru!

333
00:30:00.650 --> 00:30:03.030
No, I share in the responsibility!

334
00:30:04.710 --> 00:30:08.910
I cannot believe she did not get remarried
to someone who would protect her!

335
00:30:08.910 --> 00:30:13.740
It has already been
twenty years since I left her!

336
00:30:14.270 --> 00:30:16.500
I am on my way, Tsuru!

337
00:30:20.670 --> 00:30:22.960
Damn! It's still so far away!

338
00:30:24.780 --> 00:30:25.760
Straw Hat!

339
00:30:25.760 --> 00:30:29.470
Traffy! You think the people
of Okobore Town are okay?!

340
00:30:29.470 --> 00:30:33.390
Moron! Now do you see?
This is what happens...

341
00:30:33.390 --> 00:30:35.270
when pirates do good deeds!

342
00:30:35.270 --> 00:30:37.770
Kaido is just after us, right?!

343
00:30:37.770 --> 00:30:38.600
Yeah!

344
00:31:01.460 --> 00:31:03.170
Viceroy Kaido!

345
00:31:04.820 --> 00:31:05.800
Isn't he...

346
00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:08.010
a headliner?

347
00:31:08.010 --> 00:31:13.720
Viceroy! If you're looking for
Straw Hat Luffy and Trafalgar Law...

348
00:31:15.670 --> 00:31:19.730
they're hiding in the ruins of Oden Castle!

349
00:31:21.620 --> 00:31:23.690
Oden Castle?

350
00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:32.820
Hawkins!

351
00:31:32.820 --> 00:31:37.700
That's where Straw Hat and Law
are hiding?! Is this the truth?!

352
00:31:38.460 --> 00:31:43.500
No... I lied to him to contain his rampage.

353
00:31:44.880 --> 00:31:47.750
But that's not all.

354
00:31:48.530 --> 00:31:51.930
Maybe it's because of that
particular legend, but lately...

355
00:31:51.930 --> 00:31:56.510
people are saying that they've seen
suspicious lights on the mountain top.

356
00:31:56.510 --> 00:31:58.420
Legend?

357
00:31:58.420 --> 00:32:00.940
Do you mean the one from twenty years ago,

358
00:32:00.940 --> 00:32:05.980
where the Kozuki samurai return to enact
their revenge, even though we killed them?

359
00:32:05.980 --> 00:32:07.280
Yes.

360
00:32:07.280 --> 00:32:10.400
Instead of letting it incite
Shogun Orochi's terror,

361
00:32:10.400 --> 00:32:15.160
we can kill two birds with one stone by
letting him wipe out that abandoned castle.

362
00:32:22.020 --> 00:32:24.990
Oden Castle, you say?!

363
00:32:34.860 --> 00:32:39.960
That brings back memories...
It is indeed a good place to hide.

364
00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:42.940
So that's where they are...!

365
00:32:47.310 --> 00:32:50.730
They robbed me of my smile production.

366
00:32:50.730 --> 00:32:54.720
Those damn punks!

367
00:32:50.860 --> 00:32:55.160
"Law & Straw Hat Form Pirate Alliance"

368
00:32:56.980 --> 00:32:58.740
I won't let them get away!

369
00:33:03.690 --> 00:33:07.290
He's heading toward the ruins of Oden Castle!

370
00:33:22.990 --> 00:33:24.060
Oh?

371
00:33:27.350 --> 00:33:30.840
Hey! Isn't he coming toward us?!

372
00:33:30.840 --> 00:33:32.230
– No way!
– No way!

373
00:33:33.820 --> 00:33:36.530
Don't tell me he's noticed us!

374
00:33:36.530 --> 00:33:38.200
– What?!
– What?!

375
00:33:38.200 --> 00:33:39.620
It can't be!

376
00:33:39.620 --> 00:33:42.040
It's impossible to see us from there!

377
00:33:45.580 --> 00:33:46.620
No...

378
00:33:48.540 --> 00:33:49.590
He's coming!

379
00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:57.720
Run for it, guys!

380
00:34:05.870 --> 00:34:07.940
Why is he going over there?!

381
00:34:39.720 --> 00:34:41.140
Impossible...!

382
00:34:55.690 --> 00:34:57.400
Oh no! That's...!

383
00:35:11.870 --> 00:35:13.830
Everyone, run!

384
00:35:16.820 --> 00:35:18.880
Blast Breath!

385
00:35:44.490 --> 00:35:47.120
– Captain!
– Captain!

386
00:36:51.350 --> 00:36:55.060
Kaido!
